Critical Modifications from Original Plan
REJECTED: Complete separation of base handler classes → The original plan proposed creating entirely separate BaseCartesianHandler and BaseNonCartesianHandler classes, which violates DRY and creates unnecessary duplication. Replacement: Implemented a single BaseHandler with optional service injection and three specialized intermediate classes (CartesianChartHandler, GridChartHandler, PolarChartHandler).​

ENHANCED: Calibration service injection strategy → Original plan lacked detail on how to prevent calibration_service from being passed to non-Cartesian handlers. Addition: Implemented _initialize_handlers() with runtime type inspection using issubclass() to determine service requirements dynamically, eliminating hardcoded handler-service mappings.​

CORRECTED: Detection output format assumptions → Original plan assumed all models output standard bounding boxes. Correction: Pie charts require keypoint-based detection (5 keypoints per slice for angular geometry). Added DetectionResult unified structure supporting both bbox and keypoint outputs.​

ADDED: Missing error handling for heatmap scale → Original plan's heatmap handler lacked defensive checks for massive cell counts (10,000+ cells). Addition: Implemented spatial binning with O(N) complexity and early termination if axis labels are insufficient.​

CLARIFIED: OCR integration for new chart types → Original plan was vague about OCR processing flow. Specification: Heatmaps only OCR axis labels (not individual cells due to performance), pie charts OCR legend labels for slice matching.​

STRENGTHENED: Backward compatibility guarantees → Added explicit requirement that existing Cartesian handlers (BarHandler, ScatterHandler, etc.) must not require code changes beyond updating their base class from implicit inheritance to explicit CartesianChartHandler.​

DETAILED: Testing and validation strategy → Original plan lacked concrete testing requirements. Addition: Specified unit tests, integration tests, performance benchmarks, and regression test suite requirements (see Section 7).

🎯 DELIVERABLE 1: Refactored Handler Architecture
Rationale for This Approach
The current system suffers from tight coupling between ChartAnalysisOrchestrator and Cartesian-specific services (calibration, spatial classification). All handlers receive the same service injection regardless of whether they need those services, violating the Interface Segregation Principle.​

The original XML plan proposed creating completely separate base classes for Cartesian vs. non-Cartesian charts. This is an anti-pattern because:

Duplicates common functionality (logging, error handling, result formatting)

Makes future chart type additions require modifying multiple base classes

Violates the Open/Closed Principle (open for extension, closed for modification)

Solution: Implement a three-tier hierarchy with optional service injection:

text
BaseHandler (abstract, minimal interface)
    ├── CartesianChartHandler (requires calibration + spatial_classifier)
    ├── GridChartHandler (requires color_mapper)
    └── PolarChartHandler (requires legend_matcher)
