🎯 DELIVERABLE 2: Detection Output Structure Enhancements
Rationale
The original plan assumes all YOLO models output standard bounding boxes [x1, y1, x2, y2, conf, cls]. This is incorrect for pie charts, where we need keypoint-based detection to capture slice geometry (center point, arc start, arc end).​

Problem: The current run_inference_on_image() function in utils.py only parses bounding box outputs. Pie slice detection requires parsing keypoint arrays with shape (num_slices, 5, 3) where the last dimension is [x, y, confidence].

Solution: Create a unified DetectionResult structure that supports both detection types, and enhance inference functions to handle keypoint models.

